Geo Dove Widower with his two legitimate Children namely John Benjamin aged two Years four Months and upwards wand Charlotte aged 7 Months and upwards were removed from St CD to St Mary le Strand Geo Dove Wedn with his two legitimate Children namely Jno Benjn. 2 Yrs 4 Mths & upwds & Charlotte 7 Mths & upwds
to_place: St Mary le Strand

txt: By an Order under the Hands and Seals of J Pownall & W Addington Esqrs. two of his Majesty's Justices of the Peace in and for the County of Middx and Liberty of Westmr (one of the Quorum) Dated 12th June 1793. Ann Smith Singlewoman from St CD to St Mary le Strand Ann Smith Singlewoman
to_place: St Mary le Strand

txt: By an Order under the Hands and Seals of Wm Bleamire & Aaron Graham Esqrs. two of his Majesty's Justices of the Peace in and for the County of Middlesex and Liberty of Westmr. (one of the Quorum) Dated 18th June 1793 Ann Groves singlewoman was removed from St C D to St. Andrew Wardrobe London Ann Groves Singlewoman
to_place: St. Andrew Wardrobe London

txt: By an Order under the Hands and Seals of J Townall & A Mitchell two of his Majestys Justices of the Peace in and for the County of Midx and Liberty of Westmr (one of the Quorum) Dated 14th June 1793 Mary Gray Wife of Robt Graty them (from her) was removed from St CD to St Paul Covent Garden Mary Gray Wife of Robt. Gray then (from her)
to_place: St Paul Covent Garden

txt: Sarah Stevens (singlewoman) By an Order under the Hands & Seals of W Addington & A Mitchell Esqrs. two of his Majesty's Justices of the Peace in and for the County of Middx and Liberty of Westmr (one of the Quorum) Dated 19th June 1793 Sarah Stevens singlewoman was removed from St. C D to the Liberty of the Rolls
to_place: Liberty of the Rolls

txt: Sarah Mann Widow of John Mann By an Order under the Hands and Seals of W Kitchiner & D Walker Esqrs two of his Majesty's Justices of the Peace in and for the County of Middx and Liberty of Westminster (one of the Quorum) Dated 24th June 1793 Sarah Mann Widow of John Mann Deceased was removed from St CD to Kinsington Parish
to_place: Kinsington Parish

txt: Mary Ballard Wife of Edwd. Ballard (were then abroad) with their legitimate Child Edwd. aged 1yr.. 6th. & upwds. By an Order under the Hands and Seals of the W Addington & Edwd. Naish Esqr two of his Majesty's Justices of the Peace in and for the County of Middlesex and Liberty of Westmr. (one of the Quorum) Dated 1st July 1793 Mary Ballard Wife of Edwd Ballard (now then abroad)with there and their legitimate Child, Edward Aged 1yr, 6 Mths & upwards were removed from St C D to St Giles in the Fields
to_place: St Giles in the Fields

txt: Mary Hughes Single (Nil) No Settlemt. in the at Parish Order abandd & the Woman taken back passed to St Gregory where it also she had no Settlemt. was again taken back & removed to St. Mary whitechapel vide sabrequart Entry in the next register No'd 3 Page 4 By an Order under the Hands & Seals of N Bond & Edwd Naish Esqrs two of his Majestys Justices of the Peace in and for the County of Middx and Liberty City of Westmr. one of the Quorum) Dated the 25th July 1793, Mary Hughes was removed from Saint Clement Danes to Saint Bennett's Pauls Wharf
to_place: Saint Bennett's Pauls Wharf
